Patient: What exercise can I do to help manage my heart failure?

Healthcare Educator: Walking is a good start. Try to walk for 30 minutes a day. 

Patient: What if I get tired easily?

Healthcare Educator: Start slow. Even short walks matter. Rest when needed.

Patient: Can I do something more intense?

Healthcare Educator: Yes, but slowly increase intensity. Listen to your body.

Patient: What about swimming, is it safe?

Healthcare Educator: Absolutely, swimming is a great low-impact exercise for heart health. 

Patient: Any other exercises you would recommend?

Healthcare Educator: Yoga can be beneficial. It helps manage stress and improves heart health.